#X text 357 508 You can add transparency to the background \, which deactivates the arc! then the background is either Pd's background color or the color of an element behind it (like a [cnv] object). If you're not in theme mode \, you can still set arc color for the center circle or the the wiper., f 50;
#X text 17 115 The bgcolor \, arccolor and fgcolor parameters set background \, arc background color and foreground color with a list of RGB values (3 values from 0 to 255) or a symbol (a hexadecimal value preceded by '#' or any color name supported by tcl/tk). The "colors" message takes 3 symbols (a hex or color name) for background \, arc background and foreground \, respectively. Without an arc \, you have a full circle with the arc color., f 53;
